The paper is related to speech enhancement using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SD) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves a hybrid architecture of convolutional and recurrent networks, which is a common approach in speech processing and language modeling (cs.SD, cs.CL). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be related to machine learning optimization (cs.LG) and system design (cs.SI).
